    <img src="pics/tokyo.jpg" />
    <section class="tokyo">
      <h2> Explore Tokyo </h2>
      <ul>
        <li><h3>Popular Sites</h3></li>
          <li><h4>Tokyo Sky Tree</h4></li>
          <p> The Tokyo Sky Tree is the tallest structure in Japan. Get a great view of <br>
            mount Fuji as well as the rest of the city from over 1475 ft high!</p>
          <li><h4>Shibuya Crossing</h4><li>
          <p> The Shibuya Crossing is a famous crosswalk in the heart of Tokyo.
            surround yourself with lights and buildings, and explore all the shops
            and restaurants in Shibuya. </p>
            <p></p>
        <li><h3>Entertainment</h3></li>
          <li><h4>Roppongi</h4></li>
          <p>Exolore Tokyo's nightlife in Roppongi. Roppongi is known for having
            many bars and Restaraunts, as well as a lively night life. </p>

          <li><h4>Kabukicho (18+)</h4></li>
          <p>Exolore Tokyo's red light district in Kabukicho. Located in the district
            of Shinjuku, this area has great bars and restaurants, but is only suitable for
            18+ only. </p>
            <p></p>
        <li><h3>Restaraunts</h3></li>
        <li><h4>Ramen Shops</h4></li>
        <p> Tokyo is known to have great Ramen. Ramen shops are all over the city,
          almost on every block. </p>
        <li><h4>Uobei</h4></li>
        <p> Uobei is a fun sushi restaurants that allows you to order your meal on
          a touch screen monitor. Your meal is then sent to you on a conveyor belt right
          to your seat. Uobei has also received positive feedback on travel sites such
          as trip advisor. </p>
          <p></p>
        <li><h3>Transportation</h3></li>
        <li><h4>Tokyo Metra</h4></li>
        <p> Tokyo is known for its most efficient and advance transportation.
          You can purchase a PASMO card which will allow you to use all of the
          city's Metra trains.
        <li><h4>Bullet Train</h4></li>
        <p> Explore outside Tokyo and take a bullet train to another city such as
          Kyoto or Osaka. Japan has some of the fastest trains in the world that can
          get you to another city in half the time as driving.
      </ul>
    </section>
  </aside>
